I"i<h2 id="problem-description">Problem Description</h2>
<p>Access to energy for lighting and cooking presents a formidable obstacle to development in Nigeria. Solar energy in particular could play
a meaningful role in alleviating energy poverty in Nigeria and elsewhere. In order to provide basic information
about electricity as well as cooking fuels, the World Bank conducts “Multi-Tier Framework” surveys in conjunction with host nations.
For Nigeria, survey teams interviewed over 3,500 Nigerian households. While the trove of data is public, it is also difficult to parse
and requires additional cleaning.</p>
